DIG, IMT, and C9 would all have major issues improvising against a lane swap game due to communication issues between key roles in the swap
Scrim your challenger team or only lane swap against a specific team and boom, you both now have a pocket strategy when you're mismatched
Back when lane swapping was meta, it took you 20, 30, 40 scrims to solve the first ~15 minutes for that patch, and no ones practiced it yet
If a team in NA or EU just started lane swapping against the top of the table, they would get at least one free series win for it I'm sure
Yes, lane swapping in theory gives you an implied disadvantage early, but if you're expected to lose a standard match, spice it up
They would have to play 100% optimally on the fly and adapt to the game state, which would DESTROY these korean import rosters, for one
If I was on the bottom half of the table against a top team who enjoys drafting shen, I would challenge my opponents to a lane swap game
I wonder how far into the season it will be before we start to see some lane swaps back into the meta. Teams are not prepared for it.
